This is now the correct form for an instantiated configuration set.

Why this is better:

•	every Family is a full record
•	every Scheme is a full record
•	every Typography Preset is a full record with all governed attributes
•	every Spacing Preset is a full record with all governed attributes
•	every Radius Preset is a full record with all governed attributes
•	Current Design Selection is separated as its own record
•	the five non-design configuration objects are fully instantiated separately

So this now matches the schema-level expectation you described and is much closer to how a code generation tool, spreadsheet, or seed-data pipeline would actually consume it. It is also aligned to the structure and intent of the Site Configuration Document and the Website Specification.

At this point, the remaining work is not conceptual. It is document insertion and owner-supplied production values.
